ailable. It seems important to ensure we execute the constructor and methods in the same class to reach both call sites. Calling getParameterNames on the fixture constructor will help inspect the class, ensuring access to all methods and constructors that contain LVT info. It's a nuanced approach!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying public API needs**\\n\\nI’m reflecting on the public API requirements. I could directly use Sample.class.getDeclaredConstructor with parameters like String.class and int.class. In native tests, reflection might need metadata. However, tracking calls to Class.getDeclaredConstructor doesn’t seem relevant to coverage. The native test may indeed need reflection configuration. Even so, we want an active library call, while keeping tests outside the library package. I need to create a file with the correct package and consider using a static nested fixture.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AAAps5Vk90FkSOPAkbsO8Onz|fc_07082720c09ba69e0169f59d35410c81928ed8c1f996c15658", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 966, "output": 1179, "cacheRead": 17408, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19553, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777704228398, "responseId": "resp_07082720c09ba69e0169f59d24bd748192ae5d9f247229a5de"}}
